This paper deals with coding theory and information theory, specifically in the context of the additive white Gaussian noise channel. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of sparse codes, which falls under the category of compressed sensing, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of decoding algorithms, which could fall under cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
